<FIRST>r w PM-BombedCruiser-Accidents     10-31 0251</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bombed Cruiser-Accidents,240</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Bombed Cruiser, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Navy accident in which a fighter jet pilot
dropped a bomb on the guided missile cruiser USS Reeves was at
least the sixth aboard a Navy ship since the April 19 explosion on
the battleship USS Iowa.
   The 500-pound bomb, which officials said was ``inadvertently''
dropped on the ship Monday, blew a five-foot hole in its bow and
injured five sailors.
   Navy officials are questioning the pilot of the fighter, which
had just taken off from the carrier USS Midway. The carrier was
being escorted by the Reeves during training operations in the
Indian Ocean.
   The turret explosion aboard the USS Iowa in April killed 47
sailors.
   The other accidents, not counting sailors lost overboard,
include:
   _Oct. 29. Five sailors are killed aboard the training carrier
USS Lexington, including a Navy student pilot and four members of
the deck crew. Nineteen others were injured.
   _May 9. Six sailors are killed and five injured in a fire aboard
the USS White Plains, a supply ship, in the Atlantic.
   _May 13: Two sailors die in a pump room fire aboard the aircraft
carrier USS America in the Atlantic.
   _May 19. A Marine is drowned when a landing craft from the
amphibious landing ship USS Duluth overturns during exercises off
Australia.
   _Aug. 23. Thirty civilians are injured when a pressure relief
valve sprays visitors with hydraulic fluid and water and panic
ensues aboard the aircraft carrier USS Kennedy at Port Everglades,
Fla.
</TEXT>
