<HEAD>Snow Falls in West; East Enjoys Indian Summer</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in Montana early today, while much of the East
continued to enjoy fair weather and pleasant temperatures.
   Temperatures were expected to fall into the teens in eastern
Montana, while cold temperatures and gusty northerly winds chilled
northeast Colorado.
   North Dakota prepared for arctic temperatures, wind and snow
today, and cold temperatures with strong winds and snow were
expected in South Dakota.
   Temperatures were in the 50s and 60s throughout much of the East
early today. Fog covered much of the South, and rain fell in
Virginia and North Carolina.
   On Monday night, showers and thunderstorms extended from the
Texas Gulf Coast across eastern Texas, Louisiana and west-central
Mississippi. Rain also dampened the southeast half of Missouri,
Illinois and Wisconsin and eastern North Carolina and South
Carolina.
   Snow showers fell over southeast Minnesota and central Iowa.
   The high temperature for the nation Monday was 89 degrees in
Texas at Corpus Christi, Harlingen, Kingsville and McAllen.
