<HEAD>Oil Company Explosions Injure Two, Damage 25 Mobile Homes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREAT BEND, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A series of explosions that ripped
through an oil field service company sent explosive devices
shooting up to three-quarters of a mile away. Two workers received
minor injuries and 25 mobile homes were damaged.
   ``It was just like cannon fire,'' Police Chief Dean Akings said
in this city about 110 miles northwest of Wichita.
   Monday morning's explosions and fire at Wire Tech Service also
forced evacuation of about 200 people, authorities said. All had
returned home by late Monday except for the 25 families whose
properties were damaged.
   Fire Chief Dick Meisinger said the first blast was caused by
explosives used in the oil industry. About six more explosions and
a fire followed.
   ``There was over 1,000 of those projectiles inside the
business,'' Meisinger said. ``We've had some of those projectiles
located up to three-quarters of a mile away.''
