<HEAD>Tammy Faye Leaves After Visiting Imprisoned Husband</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLADEGA, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tammy Faye Bakker, the teary-eyed wife of
former evangelist Jim Bakker, headed home after visiting her
husband, who is serving a 45-year sentence for fraud and conspiracy.
   ``I feel like my heart is hanging on the outside of my chest,''
she said during the visit to her husband, who temporarily is being
held in a nearby medium-security federal prison.
   Since the PTL founder's arrival last week, reporters have been
at the lockup almost daily. And Mrs. Bakker has ventured out into
the community when not visiting her husband, who was convicted of
defrauding his TV followers of more than $3 million.
   After spending much of Sunday with her husband and evading press
scrutiny, Mrs. Bakker went to a dress shop in nearby Sylacauga and
chatted for 45 minutes with sales clerks.
   ``I knew it was Tammy because she had her eyebrows painted on,''
said June Harvey, 28, manager of Cato's Dress Shop. ``Nobody else
looks like that.''
   Mrs. Bakker had talked with reporters earlier in the day, tears
welling in her eyes as she prepared to leave the Colony House Motel
in Talladega for the prison.
   ``This is just so hard; it's so upsetting and I wish I could
just be upset in private,'' she said.
   Mrs. Bakker checked out of the motel Monday afternoon. She told
reporters she planned to visit her husband again before returning
home to Orlando, Fla., to be with their son, Jamie.
   Officials declined to reveal when Bakker would be transferred to
a federal prison in Rochester, Minn.
