<SECOND>PM-Lebanon-Israel, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0472,0333</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: RETRANSMITTING to CORRECT cycle designator to PMs.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Suicide Guerrilla Explodes Boat, Casualty Reports Conflict</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES thruout with Israeli army statement; background; No
pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Palestinian guerrilla blew up his boat
near an Israeli gunboat in a suicide attack in the Mediterranean
off south Lebanon and Israel said today that three sailors were
wounded.
   The Syrian-based Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine
claimed responsibility for the Monday night's attack and said
several Israelis were killed or wounded. It did not name the
attacker.
   In Jerusalem, the army said one sailor on the patrol boat was
slightly wounded and two others were ``scratched'' by shrapnel from
the explosion north of the Israeli-Lebanese border.
   News reports said the attack occurred about 12 miles north of
the border. A spokesman for the Marxist PFLP said the attack was
carried out after dark near the southern border village of Naqoura.
   The spokesman, who refused to be named, said the guerrilla was
sailing a sophisticated motorized fishing boat rigged with a large
quantity of heavy explosives.
   An Israeli radio report said an estimated 1,100 pounds of
explosives were aboard what it described as the guerrilla's rubber
dinghy.
   Sailors on the Dvora patrol boat first fired warning shots when
the guerrilla did not identify himself, then the dinghy moved
closer and exploded, an army official said on condition of
anonymity.
   Israel's navy carries out regular patrols in the area to block
guerrillas from infiltrating into Israel by sea.
   In a similar encounter April 9, an Israeli navy boat opened fire
on a rubber craft with two men aboard in the same area, killing the
two and destroying the boat. No sailors were injured.
   The worst guerrilla attack by sea was March 11, 1978 after a
13-man squad from the Palestine Liberation Organization landed in a
boat north of Tel Aviv. They then attacked two buses, killing 33
people and wounding 82.
</TEXT>
