Wendy's restaurants they operated.
   Assistant U.S. Attorney William Hogan argued, ``This is a very
dangerous man who is not at all a simple businessman.'' The
government's interest is in ``keeping alive the witnesses and their
family members,'' he said.
   Robinson was sentenced earlier this year to 10 years in prison
in the murder-for-hire of a witness to the Barber slaying. He had
been free on bail while appealing that verdict.
