<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--ChildShot     10-31 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Child Shot,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Grandfather Shoots 3-Year-Old to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANTECA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-year-old boy playing with a toy
pistol was accidentally shot to death by his grandfather who
thought his own real revolver was unloaded, police said.
   Arash Valizadeh of San Ramon was killed Monday by a gunshot
wound to the heart fired by George Clifford Lewis, 72, said Manteca
police Sgt. David Thompson.
   Lewis, who was baby-sitting at his home in this community 75
miles east of San Francisco, was treated at a hospital for chest
pains after he shot his grandson with a .22-caliber revolver,
Thompson said.
   No charges were filed.
   The boy ``said `bang, bang,' and his grandfather was joining in
the game,'' Thompson said.
   ``It's quite a tragic situation,'' Thompson said. ``It was a
typical case of not taking a gun too seriously. Time after time,
somebody gets killed with an `empty' gun.''
</TEXT>
