<SECOND>AM-BRF--Soviet-Oil,0077</SECOND>
<UNK>New Oil Deposit Found in Soviet Desert</UNK>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soviet scientists have discovered a new oil
deposit in the Kyzylkum Desert in Central Asia that will triple oil
production from Uzbekistan in several years, Tass said.
   Tass said the oil field will provide millions of tons of oil and
it is the largest deposit ever discovered in Uzbekistan or
Turkmenia.
   Uzbekistan and Turkmenia have long been key areas for Soviet oil
production.
</TEXT>
