<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SunnyLondon     10-31 0085</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Sunny London,0086</SECOND>
<HEAD>It's Official: 1989 Was Sunniest in London Since Records Began</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   With two months yet to go, weather officials have
already declared 1989 to be the sunniest year London has
experienced since records were first kept in 1929.
   Boosted by sunshine on the last two days of October, London has
recorded more than 1,770 hours of sunshine so far this year, the
London Weather Center said Tuesday.
   The previous record was set in 1976 with 1,762 hours of sun.
</TEXT>
