<HEAD>9,194 Soviet Jews Emigrate in October, 1,464 Arrive In Israel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A total of 9,194 Jews emigrated from the Soviet
Union in October, and 1,464 of them arrived in Israel, the national
news agency Itim reported Tuesday.
   Uri Gordon, head of the Immigration Department at the Jewish
Agency, a quasi-governmental body that helps handle new arrivals,
said 51,080 Jews have left the Soviet Union this year.
   Of them, 7,275 arrived in Israel, with the rest choosing to seek
resettlement elsewhere, Gordon said.
   Gordon said 284,550 Soviet Jews have requested sponsors abroad
so far this year. Israeli officials predict half will come to
Israel.
