<FIRST>r a AM-SimilarMurders     10-31 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Similar Murders,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>No Leads in Five Similar Stranglations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The strangulation deaths of five women
in the same midtown area have police investigating whether a serial
killer is at work, although police say it's too early to tell if
one person is responsible.
   The victims all were found in an area not considered a
high-crime area, said police spokesman Sgt. Greg Mills. All were
black and were found either nude or partly nude.
   Janice Berryman, 36, became the fifth victim when her body was
found Saturday in thick brush in a park. The first victim was found
Sept. 16.
   The women did not live in the immediate area where the bodies
were found, Mills said Tuesday.
   Two of the women had been involved in prostitution but three of
them had not been, he said. A dozen detectives have been assigned
to the slayings, Mills said.
   ``We need to track down their past activities and associates and
see if the friends and habits of these women cross each other,'' he
said.
   Investigators won't say whether the women were sexually
assaulted or whether the victims were believed to have been killed
where they were found.
