<FIRST>u n IndustryNews     10-31 0230</FIRST>
<SECOND>Industry News</SECOND>
<NOTE>BC-Newspapers Sold,230</NOTE>
<NOTE>Atlantic Publications Sold to The Backe Group</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ACCOMAC, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A New York communications company and an
independent investor are buying Atlantic Publications Inc., a
Virginia-based chain of more than 30 community newspapers in
Virginia, Maryland, Delaware, North Carolina and South Carolina.
   The Backe Group, headed by former CBS president John Backe, and
Susan Sounders Obrecht, an investor and president of ESS Ventures
Inc. are buying the chain in a deal expected to be completed by the
end of November.
   Terms of the sale were not disclosed.
   The chain, fouinded in 1957, also includes several seasonal,
weekly newspapers along the Atlantic coast. At peak season, the
chain has 255,000 subscribers and 200 employees.
   George N. McMath, Atlantic's president and sole stockholder,
said Tuesday that he decided to consider bids a couple of months
ago.
   ``We've always tried to stress a positive type of journalism,''
said McMath, a former state delegate and former chairman of the
state Republican Party. ``These folks seemed to share that
philosophy.''
   McMath said he will remain with the company for up to six months
during the change in ownership. He said there would be no other
personnel changes.
   Backe's company owns a number of publications, including
Gulfstream Newspapers Inc. and Gulfshore Publishing Inc.
   ESS Ventures owns and operates Mid-Atlantic Country Magazine, an
Alexandria-based monthly travel and lifestyle magazine.
