<HEAD>Bus Plunges into Ravine, 30 Killed, 22 Seriously Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COTABATO CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus plunged into a
ravine early Wednesday after it collided with a container van on a
mountain road and at least 30 people were killed and 22 seriously
injured, company officials said.
   A statement from the Mindanao Transit Corp. said the accident
occurred at 6:15 a.m. when a van sideswiped one of their buses
along a curve on a mountain road in North Cotabato, 600 miles
southeast of Manila.
   Rescuers recovered 30 bodies from the crash site, bus officials
said. They said there were at least 22 survivors with serious
injuries, including four children.
   Company officials said the casualty figure could rise as rescue
operations continued. The exact number of passengers could not be
immediately determined, they said.
