<FIRST>r f PM-AutoRecall     10-31 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Auto Recall,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Recalls '90 Escorts, '88 Tracers; Mazda Recalls 220,000 323s</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. and Mazda Motor Corp. have
announced recalls of 312,100 small cars for possible windshield and
oil system problems.
   The two companies said Monday they would replace oil filler caps
on about 8,500 1988 model Mercury Tracers and about 220,000
1986-1988 Mazda 323 automobiles with fuel-injected engines.
   Oil filler caps on the engines have no vents, which may
contribute to oil deterioration, the companies said.
   Ford also recalled about 3,600 1990-model Escort subcompacts,
saying adhesive around windshields may have been applied improperly
and the glass could pop out in a 30 mph head-on crash.
   Owners of all the vehicles were being notified by mail. Work
would be performed at no cost to the consumer.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
