<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Stocks     10-31 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Higher at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   London share prices were higher at midday Tuesday
thanks to further price markups by market makers and a trickle of
follow-through buying, but volume remained light.
   Dealers said the market started in positive territory and
shifted higher, but then began to drift from its early peaks as
buying dried up.
   At about noon in London, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index showed a 14.1 point, or 0.7 percent, rise to
2,126.3 points.
   Most dealers described the market's gains as a continuation of a
technical rally which started Monday, but felt the gains could
prove fragile if some bad news hit the market.
   Volume came to 182.8 million shares at midday, compared with
129.9 million shares at the same time Monday.
</TEXT>
