<FIRST>d f BC-SteelProduction     10-31 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Steel Production,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic steel production totaled 1,754,000
net tons during the week ended Oct. 28, 1989, down 3.4 percent from
the previous week, according to the American Iron and Steel
Institute.
   The week's production represented 78.8 percent of the industry's
domestic capacity, the steel industry group said Monday.
   American steelmakers produced 1,874,000 net tons in the same
week last year, AISI said.
   Domestic steel production so far this year is 81,934,000 net
tons, 0.6 percent below last year's production at this time, AISI
said.
   Production by district for last week (previous week in
parentheses) was:
   North East Coast 206,000 tons (229,000 tons); Pittsburgh 178,000
(177,000); Youngstown 93,000 (93,000); Lake Erie 100,000 (120,000);
Detroit 158,000 (169,000); Chicago 493,000 (497,000); Midwest
186,000 (188,000); Southern 245,000 (246,000); Western 95,000
(97,000).
</TEXT>
