<FIRST>r f PM-Earns-Whirlpool     10-31 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Earns-Whirlpool,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Whirlpool Earnings up 27.6 Percent for Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BENTON HARBOR, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Increased productivity, higher
prices and cost controls helped push Whirlpool Corp.'s
third-quarter earnings up 27.6 percent compared with last year, the
appliance maker says.
   The company said Monday it earned $46.7 million, or 68 cents a
share, during the July-September period this year, compared with
$36.6 million, or 53 cents a share, during the same time last year.
   Revenue rose to $1.5 billion this year, compared with $1.2
billion during the third quarter of last year.
   Whirlpool said the earnings came despite a drop in appliance
orders.
   For the first nine months, the company earned $137.8 million, or
$1.99 a share, up 14.5 percent from $120.4 million, or $1.74 a
share, during the same period last year.
   Year-to-date revenue for 1989 were $4.71 billion compared with
$3.39 billion last year.
</TEXT>
