<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0357</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices advanced in brisk trading today,
with paper stocks buoyed early by news of a $3 billion takeover bid.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 15.17 points at
2,618.65 after a half-hour of trading at 10 a.m. EST.
   Advancing issues outpaced decliners by nearly 3 to 1 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 737 issues up, 255 down and 423 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 21.86 million shares.
   News that Georgia Pacific Corp. had offered to acquire Great
Northern Nekoosa Corp. in a cash deal valued at more than $3
billion gave the market new life, analysts said.
   A government report suggesting the economy is growing but at a
slower pace had only a minor impact.
   The Commerce Department reported today that its chief economic
forecasting gauge inched ahead 0.2 percent in September for its
second consecutive monthly advance.
   The increase in the Index of Leading Indicators, designed to
foretell economic activity six to nine months into the future,
followed an advance of 0.5 percent in August that was revised
upward from a 0.3 percent gain reported earlier.
   ``It was O.K. data, but the real juice was the paper
consolidation,'' said Dennis Jarrett, equities analyst with Kidder,
Peabody &amp; Co. ``It gives players an excuse to come off the
sidelines and bid up paper stocks.''
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.99 at 186.58.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index had
advanced 0.87 to 369.74.
   On Monday, the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials recovered
6.76 points to 2,603.48, reversing last week's five-session losing
streak in which the blue-chip indicator lost 92.42 points.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by about 8 to 7 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
684 up, 774 down and 482 unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 126.63 million
shares, down from 170.33 million Friday and the lightest total in
three weeks.
