<FIRST>r f BC-Ford-Associates     10-31 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Ford-Associates,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Completes Acquisition of Associates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. said Tuesday it has
completed a $3.35-billion acquisition of Associates First Capital
Corp. from Paramount Communications Inc.
   Ford said Dallas-based Associates, the nation's third-largest
independent finance company based on total assets, will operate as
an independent affiliate in the Ford Financial Services Group.
   Associates has assets of about $14 billion, and has business in
real estate-secured loans, credit cards, direct installment and
revolving credit loans and mortgage banking.
   Ford Holdings Inc. was formed Sept. 1 to handle the financing
for the Associates acquisition. Included in Ford Holdings, in
addition to the Associates, is U.S. Leasing International Inc.,
Ford Leasing Development Co., The American Road Insurance Co. and
Ford Motor Land Development Corp.
   Paramount said in a separate news release that net proceeds from
the sale will total $2.6 billion, giving the company an after-tax
gain of $1.2 billion. The gain will be recorded in Paramount's
final 1989 quarter, which ended Tuesday.
