<FIRST>r f BC-Paramount-Sale     10-31 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Paramount-Sale,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Paramount Sells Two Professional Information Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paramount Communications Inc. said Tuesday it
has sold two Simon &amp; Schuster professional information services
units to the Macmillan Inc. subsidiary of the British-based media
giant Maxwell Communication Corp. PLC.
   The price was not disclosed, but a source familiar with the deal
said it was about $40 million.
   One of the units being sold is Prentice Hall Information
Services, which publishes research and information services in a
looseleaf format in areas such as taxation, pensions, financial
planning, payroll regulation, human resources management and
business law.
   Simon &amp; Schuster will retain the Corporation Law looseleaf
service which will become part of the Prentice Hall Law &amp; Business
unit.
   The other unit being sold is Prentice Hall Information Network,
which delivers electronically the PHIS tax publications and
professional tax research information.
   Paramount declined to disclose financial information about
either of the units being sold.
   The disclosure of the sale came on the same day that Paramount
said it had completed the previously disclosed $3.35 billion sale
of its financial subsidiary, Associates First Capital Corp., to a
unit of Ford Motor Co.
</TEXT>
