<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Wendy's     10-31 0262</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Wendy's,0273</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wendy's Earnings Flat in Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wendy's International Inc. said Tuesday its
third-quarter profit was the same as a year ago, when the fast-food
chain had 46 more company-owned restaurants.
   The hamburger chain said its earnings for the quarter ended Oct.
1 were $8.7 million, or 9 cents a share, on revenue of $269.2
million, compared with earnings of the same amount on revenue of
$275.2 million in the same 1988 period.
   Systemwide sales _ total sales from company and franchise
restaurants _ were $787 million, compared with $758 million in the
same period last year.
   James W. Near, president, chief executive and chief operating
officer, said there were 46 fewer company restaurants, most of
which were sold to franchise owners.
   ``We also are addressing two major concerns that have slowed our
growth _ consistency and new unit development,'' Near said in a
statement. ``In the past year we've worked very hard at improving
consistency in operations.
   ``Next year we will renew our restaurant development program and
plan to break ground on at least 100 new restaurants systemwide in
1990.''
   Earnings for the first nine months of the year rose to $24.7
million, or 26 cents per share, compared with net income of $21.7
million, or 23 cents per share, in the same period last year.
   Systemwide sales totalled $2.3 billion for the nine months this
year, compared with $2.2 billion in the same 1988 period.
   As of Oct. 1, there were 3,754 Wendy's Old Fashioned Hamburgers
restaurants worldwide, including 1,142 operated by the company.
</TEXT>
